OL,3,CWaste company fined #2.48m after
OL,4,Cworker killed by reversing truck
OL,6,FA waste management company has been
OL,7,Ffined #2.48 million after a worker was
OL,8,Fkilled by a reversing skip wagon at a
OL,9,Fsite in Bradford.
OL,11,FJames Tabiri, 57, was working as a
OL,12,Fsort line operative at Biffa Waste
OL,13,FServices Ltd's waste transfer site
OL,14,Fwhen he was crushed while walking
OL,15,Facross the weighbridge to the site
OL,16,Foffice on 10 August 2023.
OL,18,FThe company pleaded guilty to
OL,19,Fbreaching health and safety
OL,20,Fregulations.
